![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) The **Services **view allows to access your favorite Doxee Platform 3 services and view the list of all services available to your user.

- The **Favorite **section lists the services that you have marked as favorites.

- The **Services **section lists all available services, based on your access permissions.

- The **Other **section provides links to all available custom services and external services (e.g. DP2 services).

> Tip

To access the **Home &gt; Services **view, click the **ALL SERVICES **button in the Services widget on the [Home page](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-home-documentation).

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Tip

Click on the **Home **link on the breadcrumb bar at the top to go back to the Doxee Platform Home page; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Marking a service as favorite
- Move your mouse over the name of the required service.

- Click the  ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon displayed on the right to add it to your favorite services.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Important

You may favorite as many services as you like, but the Home page **Services **widget only displays the last 4 services added to your favorites.

## Accessing a service
- Move your mouse over the name of the required service.

- Click on the **Open **link displayed on the right to open the selected service in a new browser tab.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

For more information on the available Doxee Platform 3 services, see: [Doxee Platform Services Documentation](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Doxee%2BPlatform%2BServices%2BDocumentation).
